93.1.138">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/3257182/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Pseudoaneurysm+of+the+ascending+aorta+following+cardiac+surgery&amp;author=KL+Sullivan&amp;author=RM+Steiner&amp;author=SN+Smullens&amp;author=L+Griska&amp;author=SG+Meister&amp;publication_year=1988&amp;journal=Chest&amp;pages=138-143&amp;doi=10.1378%2Fchest.93.1.138&amp;pmid=3257182">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">9.</div><div id="r9" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Abbara S, Kalva S, Cury RC, Isselbacher EM. Thoracic aortic disease: spectrum of multidetector computed tomography imaging findings. <em>J Cardiovasc Comput Tomogr</em> 2007;1(1):40–54.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jcct.2007.04.003">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19083876/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Thoracic+aortic+disease%3A+spectrum+of+multidetector+computed+tomography+imaging+findings&amp;author=S+Abbara&amp;author=S+Kalva&amp;author=RC+Cury&amp;author=EM+Isselbacher&amp;publication_year=2007&amp;journal=J+Cardiovasc+Comput+Tomogr&amp;pages=40-54&amp;doi=10.1016%2Fj.jcct.2007.04.003&amp;pmid=19083876">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">10.</div><div id="r10" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Gabbieri D, Dohmen PM, Linneweber J, Lembcke A, von Heymann C, Konertz WF. Mycotic pseudoaneurysm of the ascending aorta at site of aortic cannulation. <em>Asian Cardiovasc Thorac Ann</em> 2008;16(2):e15–e17. <a href="http://asianannals.ctsnetjournals.org/cgi/reprint/